  "slug": "no-bake-chocolate-cheesecake",
  "title": "No-bake chocolate cheesecake",
  "subtitle": "Fridge-set cheesecake with dark chocolate filling",
  "excerpt": "A fridge-set cheesecake with a digestive biscuit base and a dark chocolate cream cheese filling. Melted chocolate folded into whipped cream cheese gives the filling a clean, fudge-like texture. No oven, no gelatine.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "The no-bake cheesecake is a British domestic formula of the mid-twentieth century. The chocolate version uses melted dark chocolate in place of a fruit-flavoured element. The method (whipped double cream folded into cream cheese for stability without gelatine) is the same as for any no-bake cheesecake.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "No-bake cheesecake works on one principle: whipped double cream folded into cream cheese gives the filling enough structure to hold its shape in the fridge, without gelatine. The chocolate goes in as melted dark chocolate, cooled to near room temperature before it is added.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The temperature of the melted chocolate matters. ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "Cooling the chocolate",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpaeh5lu00008wv4ypx6zqcj"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " to near room temperature before adding it to the cream cheese is important. Hot chocolate hits the cold cream cheese and seizes into grainy streaks that stay in the finished filling.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
