      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the base",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Crush the {{digestive-biscuits}} to fine crumbs. Mix with the melted {{unsalted-butter}} until evenly dampened. Press into the base of the springform tin. Refrigerate while you make the filling.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt and cool the chocolate",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt the {{dark-chocolate}} in a heatproof bowl set over a pan of barely simmering water, stirring until smooth. Remove from the heat and leave to cool for 15 to 20 minutes until it feels warm but not hot to the touch.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the filling",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the {{full-fat-cream-cheese}}, {{icing-sugar}}, and {{vanilla-extract}} together until smooth. Stir in the cooled chocolate until combined. In a separate bowl, whip the {{double-cream}} to soft peaks. Fold the whipped cream into the chocolate cream cheese in three additions.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Chill, 6 hours minimum",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Spoon onto the biscuit base and smooth the top. Refrigerate for at least 6 hours, overnight if possible. To unmould, run a warm knife around the inside of the tin before unclipping. Dust the top with {{cocoa-powder}} before serving.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
